  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Slice the <strong>aubergines</strong> into wedges</p><p>Score the <strong>aubergine flesh</strong> with a sharp knife in a criss-cross pattern, then rub the flesh with a large drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>aubergine wedges </strong>to a baking tray (or two!) and put in the oven for an initial 20 min</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1514.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1514.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1514.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1514.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1514.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the aubergine is cooking, cut the <strong>red</strong> <strong>chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p><p>Cut the<strong> cucumber</strong> in half, scrape out the inner seeds with a teaspoon and discard, then dice the <strong>deseeded cucumber</strong></p><p>Combine the<strong> rice vinegar</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>diced</strong> <strong>cucumber</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a bowl – this is your <strong>quick-pickled cucumber</strong></p>",
